lin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=793.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok....fork over the info..</span><hr size=1> You know, I recognize the truth of what Talaban says - yes Verant has stated that epic quests are, well &quot;EPIC&quot; and not everyone will get one of these.  But every time someone points this out publicly, the adventurer in me says, &quot;Why not me?&quot;  In other words, while I know it isn't necessarily the intent of those who quote the &quot;not for everybody&quot; line, what people hear them say is &quot;Bombair, you don't deserve an epic - they're reserved for people more special than you.&quot;  Let's face it -- we play this game to be the heroes and adventurers and swashbucklers we can't be in real life and no one is going to say, &quot;Well, that epic is not for everybody so I should just give up -- I'm not worthy.&quot;  Hell, no!  I believe I am good at what I do and believe I AM worthy and if I didn't, I should have retired my character long ago.  So the fact is, while it may not happen, I WILL strive for my epic weapon and furthermor, I WILL believe it is my right to do so and take my best shot.  And if that takes some political expertise as well as tactical, then I'll brush up on my politics.  I don't care who you are, guilded or not, you have every right to make the effort.<br><br>Steppy Astravox<br>Acting Guild Leader<br>The Stryngs of Ayre <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=793.topic&start=21&stop=21>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showPrevMessage?topicID=793.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showNextMessage